.

Insert a row containing a string into the table.

var key = "myKey";
Prime.SharedStorageService.InsertRowAtTable(key, "Hello World!", Context.DUT, ResetPolicy.RESET_AT_DEVICE_START, this.SessionContext);.

Insert a row containing an object of type T into the table.

// storing the object...
var key = "myKey";
var myObj = new MyObject();
Prime.SharedStorageService.InsertRowAtTable>MyObject<(key, myObj, Context.DUT, ResetPolicy.RESET_AT_DEVICE_START, this.SessionContext);.

Returns a copy of the object stored using the key provided.
See example below:

// storing the object...
var key = "myKey";
var myObj = new MyObject();
Prime.SharedStorageService.InsertRowAtTable>MyObject<(key, myObj, Context.DUT, ResetPolicy.RESET_AT_DEVICE_START, this.SessionContext);
// retrieving the object using the same string
var myObj = Prime.SharedStorageService.GetRowFromTable<MyObject>(key, Context.DUT, this.SessionContext);

Attempt to get a row from the table using the provided key. If the row exists,
the value of the row is returned.

(bool found, MyObject myObj) = Prime.SharedStorageService.TryGetValue<myObj>("key", Context.DUT, sessionContext);
if (found)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"My stored object=[key]=[{storedObject.ToString()}]");
}
else
{
    Console.WriteLine($"My stored object with key=[key] not found");
}
